value.text: sense 2 is a close match although it mixes concept and category on one hand with a designation on the other hand. And these two seem fundamentally different: designation is a word or phrase, isn't it?

other online dicts do not have anything corresponding; further clarification would perhaps require Wiktionary' attestation methodology to see whether en:notion is in fact used as a synonym of en:concept. Wikidata is not suited for this since it deals with concepts, not words (except for lexemes).
Not conceptually accurate since the object, concept clarification, is an activity, not a field of study. How to say this better?
